so
clean in any other way. John, who
used
the common way of taking water in
his hand, to
wash
his face, was
displeased
with Roger's innovation, and
remonstrated
against
it. The
remonstrance
had no
other effect, than to fix Roger's opinion
more firmly, and as a farther
